			<div class='culture-prompt'>
				<h2 class="h2-heading">Culture</h2>
				<p class="p-content">China’s culture is one of the richest in the world dating back nearly thousands of years ago.  Much of the art is influenced by the country’s history due to its spiritual and mystical characteristics.  Writing and calligraphy are also two important forms of art as well as its sculptures and pottery.  China’s performing arts are also a big part of its culture ranging from its martial arts of Kungfu, traditional folk dances, acrobatics, as well as shadow plays. </p>
				<p class="p-content">Although not as relevant today, religion was an important aspect that helped to shape the country’s culture from its “three teachings.”  These teachings refer to the combination of Confucianism, Taoism, and Buddhism.  These religions/philosophies are still relevant today although in much smaller numbers, however, its teachings are still prevalent in the country’s culture.</p>
				<p class="p-content">Another important aspect of China’s culture is its strong family ties.  Traditionally, the structure of Chinese families has been rigid and hierarchical which is evident in today’s age with many being taught to honor one’s parents or ancestors.  With how much has changed in China’s culture in the last hundred years, this family structure has had to evolve with this change.  Young members of families often move to prosperous cities for work related reasons, however, pressure to marry and move back home increases around the age of thirty.</p>
			</div>


